Package ohos.data.orm

Interface EntityHelper<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Indicates the OrmObject instance.

    public interface EntityHelper<T>
    Provides the helper interface for operating OrmObject objects.

    The ORM annotation processor automatically generates a helper class inherited from EntityHelper for each entity class that is inherited from OrmObject and annotated with @Entity. In this case, your application does not need to implement and invoke this method.

    Since:
    1
    SystemCapability
    SystemCapability.Data#DATA_APPDATAMGR

        void bindValue​(Statement statement,
               T object)
        Binds attribute values of an inserted OrmObject object to the database declaration statement. This method is used to bind attribute values of an OrmObject object to the database declaration statement when inserting the object into the database. Your application does not need to implement and invoke this method.

        statement - Indicates the database declaration statement.

               T object,
               long id)
        Binds attribute values of an updated OrmObject object to the database declaration statement. This method is used to bind attribute values of an OrmObject object to the database declaration statement when updating the object in the database. Your application does not need to implement and invoke this method.
        Parameters:
        statement - Indicates the database declaration statement.
        object - Indicates the OrmObject object.
        id - Indicates the ID of the row where the object is updated.
